A candidate in Homa Bay county collapsed on Tuesday morning during KCPE exams.Brenda Achieng', 14, is said to have collapsed while taking the Mathematics paper at Ogenga Primary School.Area subcounty Education director Sospeter Were said the girl lost consciousness just before the second paper, English Grammar.He said Achieng' was taken to Ramula subcounty hospital for treatment."We had to assign other invigilators to supervise the girl to enable her take the papers in the hospital," he said.He said the girl was diagnosed with strong malaria.The director assured Achieng's parents that she will do the remaining papers in the hospital if she is not discharged by Wednesday."Let's give pupils a conducive environment for exams," he said.